        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/tomatoplant/{size}/31888_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-04-23T13:11:37.714Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Letâ€™s do some quick math. Letâ€™s say that the whistleblower has a 8 core CPU computer and that we are looking at a 1 minute PoW target (something that in my opinion is too much and makes bad UX, but this is another topic). <a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/ec2/pricing/on-demand/\">AWS offers a 8 core CPU with 32GiB of RAM at 0.2688USD/hour</a>, this means that for 0.27$ we can get 60 spam accounts while the whistleblower got 1. If we scale this method to an arbitrary with some serious resources, letâ€™s say 10000USD (which is not that much, if we are talking about the US Government), they could create 37000 spam accounts. You can easily see how overwhelming a whistleblower tip-line with this amount of fake accounts wouldnâ€™t be that difficult, and thereâ€™s cheaper ways to rent a computer to generate Signal accounts.</p>",
