        "created_at": "2025-04-23T13:35:43.121Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Youâ€™ve set the cost too low. Assume 1 day PoW with 8 core CPU.</p>\n<p>Now the attacker also has spend 1 day work on 8-core CPU per account</p>\n<p>Whatever number of CPU hours the honest user spends, the attacker also has to spend same number of CPU hours.</p>\n<p>Iâ€™m assuming attacker also purchases their own hardware (which is cheaper than AWS).</p>\n<p>What the attacker can do is purchase an ASIC. With an ASIC-resistant algo like moneroâ€™s, the attacker gets maybe 10x hashes per dollar compared to the honest user.</p>\n<p>I agree UX of spending 1 day on PoW is not ideal, but it could run as a background process and allow pausing midway. Itâ€™ll only be used in a small minority of cases where purchasing a SIM card under your real name is considered risky.</p>",
