    "excerpt": "<p>This wouldâ€™t reduce spam, as the computation and memory bandwith difference between a budget phone and a server grade machine is abysmal, so an attacker could create many accounts at a insignificant price if you still allow low-end devices in the network. In addition, set-up of an account would take more time, which would make some users abandon the process alltogether.<br>\nAll in all, PoW is not a good method to prevent spam when your clients have to run on mobile devices</p>"
